name: Unidentified_Twi%27lek_(3rd_Moon)
content:
Around 3 ABY, a blue-skinned Twi'lek played the mercenary Sana Starros at a game of Dejarik on the Outer Rim Territories' 3rd Moon. During the game, the pair drew blasters on each other. In the midst of the standoff, an alien brough a holocomm that had been hailed for Starros. The mercenary then fatally shot the Twi'lek in the head and additionally killed a number of other aliens around the table, taking the holocomm to speak with her contactor, the Rebel Alliance General Hera Syndulla. While Starros spoke with Syndulla, she stole a bag from the Twi'lek's corpse, which was slumped over the Dejarik table.
The Twi'lek first appeared in the twentieth issue of the 2016 Star Wars: Doctor Aphra comic series, written by Si Spurrier, illustrated by Kev Walker, and published by Marvel Comics on May 23, 2018.
